  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "body": "During testing a AWS cluster, found AWS volume once was pending for detach about 30 minutes. According to the log, the following happened,\n- controller issues a detach operation\n- after detach response returns, it periodically checks the status until it reaches \"detached\". However, in this test, the status is \"busy\" all the time. \n- after reaching the timeout 30 mins, detach function returns error because the status is not \"detached\"\n\nThe following is the log related to the failed test\n\nI0915 18:29:46.470405       5 operation_executor.go:649] Verified volume is safe to detach for volume \"kubernetes.io/aws-ebs/aws://us-west-2a/vol-540bc3dc\" (spec.Name: \"pvc-540ccbfc-7ac7-11e6-abe5-02a41bd7f415\") from node \"ip-172-20-0-244.us-west-2.compute.internal\".\nE0915 18:59:54.924434       5 attacher.go:206] Error detaching volumeID \"vol-540bc3dc\": Timeout waiting for volume state: actual=busy, desired=detached\nE0915 18:59:54.924496       5 nestedpendingoperations.go:253] Operation for \"\\\"kubernetes.io/aws-ebs/aws://us-west-2a/vol-540bc3dc\\\"\" failed. No retries permitted until 2016-09-15 18:59:55.424472076 +0000 UTC (durationBeforeRetry 500ms). Error: DetachVolume.Detach failed for volume \"kubernetes.io/aws-ebs/aws://us-west-2a/vol-540bc3dc\" (spec.Name: \"pvc-540ccbfc-7ac7-11e6-abe5-02a41bd7f415\") from node \"ip-172-20-0-244.us-west-2.compute.internal\" with: Timeout waiting for volume state: actual=busy, desired=detached\n",
  "closed_at": "2017-02-16T07:01:07Z",
